xt":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ובשלוחו","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"ובשלוחו","type":"text"}],"pathString":"ובשלוחו","enclosingTopic":"Mishnah on Kiddushin 41a","enclosingSubtopic":"Full Text"}],"direction":"rtl"},{"tokens":[{"text":"The Mishnah begins: האיש, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"ha’ish","type":"text"}]},{"text":", “the man,” מקדש, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"mekadesh","type":"text"}]},{"text":", “is/is being ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"mekadesh","type":"text"}]},{"text":",” ie, he is creating the ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"kiddushin","type":"text"}]},{"text":" stage of marriage with a woman (which is prior to the second stage of ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"nisuyin","type":"text"}]},{"text":" after which they will be formally married.)","type":"text"}],"type":"text-line"},{"tokens":[{"text":"When the Mishnah describes an ongoing action like this, ie “the man is being mekadesh”, we understand it to be telling us that the described action is ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"mutar lechatchila","type":"text"}]},{"text":", ie, perfectly acceptable to do, as opposed to if the Mishnah would have used a past-tense verb (eg “the man was ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"mekadesh","type":"text"}]},{"text":"”) which would imply the action is only permissible ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"bedieved","type":"text"}]},{"text":", ie if already done it can be relied upon.","type":"text"}],"type":"text-line"},{"tokens":[{"text":"So to recap, האיש מקדש, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"ha’ish mekadesh","type":"text"}]},{"text":", a man is permitted to be mekadesh, בו,  ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"bo","type":"text"}]},{"text":", “via himself,” ובשלוחו, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"ub’shlucho","type":"text"}]},{"text":", and (ie or) “via his shaliach.” Ie, either of these are perfectly acceptable and effective ways of producing the ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"kiddushin","type":"text"}]},{"text":" state.","type":"text"}],"type":"text-line"},{"type":"table_list","alignment":"right","rtl":false,"items":[{"list":false,"hidden":false,"tokens":[{"text":"Continue","type":"local","tokens":[{"text":"Continue","type":"text"}],"targetSubtopic":"Mishnah 2","targetTopic":"Mishnah on Kiddushin 41a","enclosingTopic":"Mishnah on Kiddushin 41a","enclosingSubtopic":"Full Text"}]}]}],"Mishnah 2":[{"type":"block_quote","tokens":[{"text":"האשה","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"האשה","type":"text"}],"pathString":"האשה","enclosingTopic":"Mishnah on Kiddushin 41a","enclosingSubtopic":"Mishnah 2"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"מתקדשת","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"מתקדשת","type":"text"}],"pathString":"מתקדשת","enclosingTopic":"Mishnah on Kiddushin 41a","enclosingSubtopic":"Mishnah 2"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"בה","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"בה","type":"text"}],"pathString":"בה","enclosingTopic":"Mishnah on Kiddushin 41a","enclosingSubtopic":"Mishnah 2"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ובשלוחה","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"ובשלוחה","type":"text"}],"pathString":"ובשלוחה","enclosingTopic":"Mishnah on Kiddushin 41a","enclosingSubtopic":"Mishnah 2"}],"direction":"rtl"},{"tokens":[{"text":"The Mishnah continues: האשה, “the woman,” מתקדשת, “is becoming mekudeshes,” ie, is entering the kiddushin stage of marriage. ","type":"text"}],"type":"text-line"},{"type":"table_list","alignment":"right","rtl":false,"items":[{"list":false,"hidden":false,"tokens":[{"text":"Continue","type":"local","tokens":[{"text":"Continue","type":"text"}],"targetSubtopic":"Mishnah 3","targetTopic":"Mishnah on Kiddushin 41a","enclosingTopic":"Mishnah on Kiddushin 41a","enclosingSubtopic":"Mishnah 2"}]}]}],"Mishnah 3":[{"type":"block_quote","tokens":[{"text":"האיש","